Yep, its annoying.
The void promise was apparently done for "performance" reasons, but I remember removing it last year and I couldn't see any performance difference.
We need to do something like this:
channel.writeAndFlush(sendBuf).addListener(res -> {
            if (!res.isSuccess()) {
                // fail with unavailable?
                CompletableFuture<TurboAPI.BaseCommand> resp = pendingRequests.remove(requestId);
                if (resp != null && !resp.isDone()) {
                    // res.cause()
                    resp.completeExceptionally(res.getThrowable());
                }
            }
        });

